		<div id="comment_body_65014499">PoE switches are pretty cheap now days.  If getting one for noise sensitive area get a fan-less one.  If noise not a problem a retired one from commercial use can be a real bargain.  That was the easy part.  The hard part was getting my servers correctly set up for RPi PXE booting.  Also ended up creating tool to manage file system images on the server so a could add RPi and change their OSes easier.  A bit like Docker but with real hardware.</div>
	</div>

