		on Saturday December 14, 2024 @07:21PM (<span class="ind"></span><a rel="nofollow" href="//build.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23551789&amp;cid=65013987">#65013987</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65013987"><p>The latest RPi 5 is really great running off an M.2 or external USB-C SSD attached... every bit as good as a mainstream laptop/desktop for basic tasks. Running off a microSD is much less pleasant. You could still use an external USB drive with the Pi 500, but it would have cost so little to include an M.2 slot on this and would have made it so much nicer. Really poor decision-making from RPi.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65013987">
